SIMPLE: undercut
RECORDS: 3

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Undercut
<hw>Un"der*cut`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>The lower or under
side of a sirloin of beef; the fillet.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Undercut</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Undercut
<hw>Un`der*cut"</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>To
cut away, as the side of an object, so as to leave an overhanging
portion.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>to sell goods or services at a price below that of
(the competition or a competitor's price).</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>to weaken the effectiveness of; to undermine or
sabotage (an activity).</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

<p><sn>4.</sn> <fld>(Forestry)</fld> <def>To cut a notch in one side of
(a tree) so as to control the direction in which the tree falls when it
is felled.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Undercut</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 3 ====
HEADWORD: Undercut
<hw>Un"der*cut`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>p. a.</pos> <def>Cut away
below.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Underdealing</ent>⟦br⟧
